<title type="html"><![CDATA[6/6(Sat.) 9 Healthy Foods That Lift Your Mood / The Art of Adding to Your Life By Subtracting From It]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=399&amp;p=416#p416"><![CDATA[
6/6(Sat.)<br />9 Healthy Foods That Lift Your Mood / The Art of Adding to Your Life By Subtracting From It<br />session 1.<br />9 Healthy Foods That Lift Your Mood<br />When you’re feeling down, it can be tempting to turn to food to lift your spirits. However, the sugary, high calorie treats that many people resort to have negative consequences of their own.Thus, you may wonder whether any healthy foods can improve your mood.<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.healthline.com/nutrition/mood-food">https://www.healthline.com/nutrition/mood-food</a><!-- m --><br /><br />1.Do you think that eating food can improve your mood?<br />2.When you’re in a bad mood, what kind of food you would like to eat?<br />3. According to this article, what types of food can improve your emotional health?<br />4.How often do you eat deep-sea fish (e.g., tuna and salmon)? In contrast to freshwater fish, which one do you prefer? Why?<br />5. Do you have the habit of drinking beverages (such as coffee, tea, fruit juice, beer, and soft drink) every day? In what context did you start this habit? Can it affect your physical or emotional health? Please share your experience.<br /><br />session 2.<br />The Art of Adding to Your Life By Subtracting From It<br />To improve your life and well-being, the immediate attempt is to add more to it, to increase and expand. That works, but only to a certain degree. It can actually reduce the quality of it. By practicing via negativa – the art of adding to your life by subtracting – you can make it better by hacking away the unessential.<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://siimland.com/via-negativa-art-a">https://siimland.com/via-negativa-art-a</a><!-- m --> ... btracting/<br /><br />1. With your present lifestyle, how busy are you? Do you enjoy being busy? Or, do you want to be busier? No matter what kind of situation you are in, by adding or subtracting something, which way is more helpful for you?<br />2. Subtracting things from our life is necessary but not easy. Have you succeeded in subtracting things from life and ended up improving the quality of your life?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=25764">Michelle Hsu</a> — Fri Jun 05, 2020 9:46 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
